{"id": 18298, "date": "2020-05-26T05:00:00", "date_gmt": "2020-05-26T12:00:00", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=18298"}, "modified": "2020-05-25T19:43:44", "modified_gmt": "2020-05-26T02:43:44", "slug": "cover-me-jericho-seb-martel-the-ghost-of-tom-joad", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2020/05/26/cover-me-jericho-seb-martel-the-ghost-of-tom-joad/", "title": {"rendered": "Cover Me, Jericho &#038; Seb Martel: The Ghost of Tom Joad"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>Wow.</p>\n<p>There&#8217;s an absolute flood of Springsteen covers being released by artists during the global shutdown, and while I try to watch them all, it&#8217;s tough to find the time or the quiet to pay full attention.</p>\n<p>But when I came across this cover of &#8220;<a href=\"http://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2019/10/17/roll-of-the-dice-the-ghost-of-tom-joad/\">The Ghost of Tom Joad</a>&#8221; by French singer-songwriter Jericho with Seb Martel on lap steel, I found myself unable to look away.</p>\n<p>This may be the single most impassioned performance (in acoustic form, at least) I&#8217;ve ever heard of Bruce&#8217;s oft-covered song.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"THE GHOST OF TOM JOAD (cover acoustic live) / Jericho &amp; Seb Martel\" width=\"758\" height=\"426\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/qt9GpDjeSGI?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n<p>Jericho&#8217;s cover is intended to raise awareness for relief efforts in Montreuil, a Parisian suburb. There&#8217;s no link in the video for donations, though, just instructions for locals who want to help.</p>\n<p>So if you&#8217;re moved by his outstanding cover and want to help but aren&#8217;t local, perhaps find an organization working to help struggling families in our own communities.</p>\n<p>Stay healthy, and stay safe.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>Jericho and Seb Martel&#8217;s cover of &#8220;The Ghost of Tom Joad&#8221; is impassioned, heartfelt, and timely&#8211;one of the best covers of Bruce&#8217;s all-too-relevant song.</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 18792, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_active": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_note": "", "_monsterinsights_sitenote_category": 0, "jetpack_post_was_ever_published": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_access": "", "_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content": false, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content": false, "footnotes": "", "jetpack_publicize_message": "", "jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled": true, "jetpack_social_post_already_shared": true, "jetpack_social_options": {"image_generator_settings": {"template": "highway", "default_image_id": 0, "font": "", "enabled": false}, "version": 2}}, "categories": [4], "tags": [2770, 2771, 582], "class_list": ["post-18298", "post", "type-post", "status-publish", "format-standard", "has-post-thumbnail", "hentry", "category-cover-me", "tag-jericho", "tag-seb-martel", "tag-the-ghost-of-tom-joad"], "aioseo_notices": [], "jetpack_publicize_connections": [], "jetpack_featured_media_url": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/jericho.jpg?fit=960%2C960&ssl=1", "jetpack_sharing_enabled": true, "jetpack_shortlink": "https://wp.me/p9w3Lk-4L8", "jetpack_likes_enabled": true, "jetpack-related-posts": [{"id": 16772, "url": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2020/04/04/cover-me-tom-morello-roger-waters-and-the-wounded-warriors-band-the-ghost-of-tom-joad/", "url_meta": {"origin": 18298, "p